# =============================================================================
# Title:   Exercise 3.2 — Reification approach 3: Named graphs
# Purpose: Same fact in TriG format (Turtle + named graphs). The assertions
#          go inside a named graph; metadata triples describe the graph itself.
#          Format: TriG (file extension .trig). Fuseki loads TriG natively.
# Date:    2026-06-03
# Author:  Barbara Hidalgo-Sotelo (Sensemaking AI)
# =============================================================================

@prefix rdf:         <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs:        <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix xsd:         <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix dcterms:     <http://purl.org/dc/terms/> .
@prefix prov:        <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#> .
@prefix schema:      <https://schema.org/> .
@prefix naruto:      <https://sensemaking-ai.com/ns/naruto#> .
@prefix sensemaking: <https://sensemaking-ai.com/ns/> .

# ── Named graph 1: The manga chapter 401 revelation ──────────────────────────
# The assertions about Itachi go INSIDE this named graph.
# The graph IRI (naruto:MangaSource401) is itself a node in the default graph
# that can carry metadata triples.

naruto:MangaSource401 {
    naruto:ItachiUchiha naruto:killedClan     naruto:UchihaClan .
    naruto:ItachiUchiha naruto:actedUnderOrders naruto:DanzoShimura .
    naruto:ItachiUchiha naruto:motivation     naruto:ProtectKonoha .
}

# ── Named graph 2: The earlier, contradictory narrative ───────────────────────
naruto:MangaSource131 {
    naruto:ItachiUchiha naruto:killedClan  naruto:UchihaClan .
    naruto:ItachiUchiha naruto:motivation  naruto:PersonalAmbition .
}

# ── Default graph: metadata about each named graph ────────────────────────────
# Provenance, source, date, and confidence for each graph live here.
# A query can join the named graph (for the assertions) with the default graph
# (for the metadata) using FROM / FROM NAMED / GRAPH patterns.

{
    naruto:MangaSource401
        a prov:Entity , schema:Book ;
        schema:name        "Naruto manga, vol. 43, ch. 401"@en ;
        dcterms:date       "2007-05-14"^^xsd:date ;
        dcterms:isPartOf   naruto:NarutoMangaSeries ;
        sensemaking:confidence sensemaking:CanonicalManga ;
        rdfs:comment       "The revelation chapter. Itachi's motivations reframed as sacrifice rather than ambition. This contradicts assertions in earlier source graphs."@en .

    naruto:MangaSource131
        a prov:Entity , schema:Book ;
        schema:name        "Naruto manga, vol. 15, ch. 131"@en ;
        dcterms:date       "2002-06-03"^^xsd:date ;
        dcterms:isPartOf   naruto:NarutoMangaSeries ;
        sensemaking:confidence sensemaking:CanonicalDisputed ;
        rdfs:comment       "Early portrayal of Itachi's motivation — later retconned by ch. 401."@en .
}

# ── Querying named graphs ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# In SPARQL, named graphs are queried with the GRAPH keyword:
#
# SELECT ?assertion ?source ?confidence WHERE {
#   GRAPH ?g { naruto:ItachiUchiha naruto:killedClan naruto:UchihaClan . }
#   ?g dcterms:date ?date ;
#      sensemaking:confidence ?confidence ;
#      schema:name ?source .
# }
# ORDER BY ?date
#
# This returns each named graph that contains the assertion, with its metadata.
# Named graphs are the most natural reification for "all facts from this source."

# ── Advantage and limitation ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Advantage: granularity at the graph level, not the triple level. All
# assertions from a single chapter go in one named graph with one set of
# metadata triples. Querying is clean with GRAPH patterns.
# Limitation: you cannot annotate individual triples within the named graph
# without classical or RDF-star sub-annotation. Named graphs annotate groups
# of assertions, not single triples.
